{"type":"message","id":"997c9f5e","parentId":"219c2421","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:14:59.393Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting the Filesystem**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm currently reviewing the filesystem output, which shows a list of files with their associated timestamps and sizes. I am now beginning to parse through these files to understand their relationships and potential dependencies. I'm focusing on the agent-related files first.\n\n\n**Finding the Target File**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI've located the `bot.py` file within the `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main` subdirectory. My initial scan of the root directory didn't reveal it; my apologies. Now, I'm ready to begin reading the contents of `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/bot.py`, after correcting that misstep.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771161299389_72","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/bot.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":12993,"output":320,"cacheRead":12531,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13313,"cost":{"input":0.025986,"output":0.00384,"cacheRead":0.0025062,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0323322}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771161293310}}
{"type":"message","id":"6644e68b","parentId":"997c9f5e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:14:59.411Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771161299389_72","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\r\nimport logging\r\nimport os\r\nfrom ai import load_ai\r\nfrom telegram.ext import ApplicationBuilder, ContextTypes, CommandHandler, MessageHandler, filters\r\nfrom telegram import Update\r\n\r\nlogging.basicConfig(\r\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\r\n    level=logging.INFO\r\n)\r\n\r\nclass TelegramBot:\r\n    def __init__(self, token):\r\n        self.app = ApplicationBuilder().token(token).build()\r\n        # Ensure API key is available\r\n        api_key = os.environ.get(\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\", \"YOUR_API_KEY_HERE\")\r\n        self.ai = load_ai(api_key=api_key)\r\n\r\n    async def start(self, update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\r\n        await context.bot.send_message(\r\n            chat_id=update.effective_chat.id, \r\n            text=\"I'm a lightweight bot powered by Gemini 1.5 Flash!\"\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    async def chat(self, update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\r\n        user_message = update.message.text\r\n        # Async-friendly AI call\r\n        # Note: Gemini calls block, so ideally this should be run in executor for high load,\r\n        # but for a simple bot, this is fine or can be awaited if the wrapper supports it.\r\n        # Here we assume a synchronous call for simplicity or wrap it if needed.\r\n        response = self.ai.generate_response(user_message)\r\n        await context.bot.send_message(chat_id=update.effective_chat.id, text=response)\r\n\r\n    def run(self):\r\n        start_handler = CommandHandler('start', self.start)\r\n        chat_handler = MessageHandler(filters.TEXT & (~filters.COMMAND), self.chat)\r\n        \r\n        self.app.add_handler(start_handler)\r\n        self.app.add_handler(chat_handler)\r\n        \r\n        self.app.run_polling()\r\n\r\nif __name__ == '__main__':\r\n    TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\", \"YOUR_BOT_TOKEN\")\r\n    bot = TelegramBot(TOKEN)\r\n    bot.run()\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771161299409}}
